{"about_the_game":"<p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>&quot;Lost Infinity&quot; is a linear visual novel with thriller elements. Heavy, oppressive atmosphere, bleak landscapes of the future, a sense of longing and alienation, with a small and false ray of hope.</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2583530/extras/wishlist_english.png?t=1738894175\" /></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2583530/extras/gameplay-english_2.gif?t=1738894175\" /></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>The world of dystopia. What's wrong with it and how did it get that way? I don't think it matters. What matters is who we are in it. Biological machines or human beings? Nobody cares about each other, there's no family, morality doesn't matter. There is only purpose. A great purpose. But can we be sure we know what we're aiming for? Are we sure we need it? And when can we see a piece of this inescapable, all-powerful and all-consuming infinity?</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> <br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2583530/extras/1201__3__1_.gif?t=1738894175\" /></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>The protagonist Faith wakes up in the evening in his apartment. An unknown desire pulls him to the street tonight. There he finds the corpse of a beautiful girl. He has often found the bodies of people in this city, but for some reason just today it seemed wrong to him, just today nothing will change, just today nothing is unknown, just today...</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> <br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2583530/extras/dog-englis